### Format Rules

**Checkboxes are mandatory.** Every actionable item in Tasks AND Verification MUST have a `- [ ]` checkbox. No exceptions.

**Group tasks by section** using `### Section Name`. Each section maps to a visual section of the landing page.

**Separate title from description.** The checkbox line has the bold task title only. Description follows on the next line(s).

**Include content source references.** Each section task should reference `copy.md` as the content source (written by the next step).

## Guardrails

- **Always save the plan file** — The outline MUST be written to `{{task.changePath}}/tasks.md`. An outline only shown in chat is a failure.
- **Always present for approval** — After saving, show the file path and summary in chat. The user must approve the LP structure before copy begins.
- **Outline, don't build** — Do NOT write code, create files, or implement anything. The outline is the deliverable.
- **Outline, don't write copy** — Do NOT write headlines, body text, or CTA text. Use placeholder descriptions like "Content source: copy.md hero section". The copy step writes the actual text.
- **Section order matters** — The order defines the scroll experience. Justify the sequence based on conversion psychology and market analysis findings.
- **Include the differentiator** — Every outline MUST have a Product Differentiator section. This is the custom interactive widget that makes the LP unique. It is NOT a generic feature grid.
- **Next.js SSG** — The implementation should target Next.js with static rendering for SEO. Make this explicit in the project setup tasks.
- **Strict format only** — 5 top-level sections: `# Plan:`, `## Summary`, `## Context`, `## Tasks`, `## Verification`. No extras.
- **No horizontal rules** — Tasks are separated by blank lines only.

